commit.message:
Fix failing i18n tests

These were (presumably) broken by commit
e23e4d04a8f69b0853164ee3667e52e731006c36, as per Qt's docs:

> Note: Some compilers have bugs encoding strings containing
> characters outside the US-ASCII character set. Make sure you
> prefix your string with u in those cases. It is optional
> otherwise.

In this case, it's needed for MSVC compilers on AppVeyor.
